modules.description: Provides interface definitions for implementing network protocols including Ethernet, ARP, IP (IPv4/IPv6), ICMP (ICMPv4/ICMPv6), UDP (UDPv4/UDPv6), and TCP (TCPv4/TCPv6). Operates with protocol-specific type signatures for packet parsing, transmission, and handling. Used to standardize network stack components in MirageOS-based systems.

Provides pretty-printers for errors and IP addresses, and supports demultiplexing incoming IP packets to TCP or UDP handlers. Enables sending IP packets with customizable headers, fragmentation, and TTL, and calculates pseudoheaders for checksums. Manages IP address configuration, retrieves source addresses, and determines maximum transmission unit for a given destination.
